static IProducer<Message<T> > Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Merge< T > ( IEnumerable< IProducer< T >>  inputs,
DeliveryPolicy< T >  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Merge one or more streams (T) into a single stream (Message{T}) interleaved in wall-clock time.

Messages are produced in the order they arrive, in wall-clock time; potentially out of originating-time order.

Template Parameters
TType of messages.
Parameters
inputsCollection of homogeneous inputs.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of merged messages.

◆ Merge< T >() [2/2]

IProducer< T >  input2,
DeliveryPolicy< T >  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Merge two streams (T) into a single stream (Message{T}) interleaved in wall-clock time.

Messages are produced in the order they arrive, in wall-clock time; potentially out of originating-time order.

Template Parameters
TType of messages.
Parameters
input1First input stream.
input2Second input stream with same message type.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of merged messages.

static IProducer<double> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Min ( this IProducer< double >  source,
DeliveryPolicy< double >  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Compute the minimum of a stream of double values.

Parameters
sourceThe source stream.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of minimum values.

This operator considers the minimum of a number and NaN to be NaN. Consequently, once a value of NaN is encountered on the source stream, the corresponding output value and all subsequent output values will be NaN.

◆ NullableSelect< TIn, TOut >() [1/2]

static IProducer<TOut?> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.NullableSelect< TIn, TOut > ( this IProducer< TIn?>  source,
Func< TIn, Envelope, TOut >  selector,
DeliveryPolicy< TIn?>  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Executes a transform function for each non-null item in the input stream, generating a new stream with the values returned by the function, or null if the input was null. The function has access to the envelope of the input message.

Template Parameters
TInThe input message type.
TOutThe output message type.
Parameters
sourceThe source stream to subscribe to.
selectorThe function to perform on every message in the source stream. The function takes two parameters, the input message and its envelope.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
A stream of type TOut .
Type Constraints
TIn :struct 
TOut :struct

Parameters
sourceSource stream.

DeliveryPolicy< TIn[]>  deliveryPolicy = null,
string  name = null,
DeliveryPolicy  defaultParallelDeliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Transforms a stream of fixed-size array messages by creating a stream for each element in the array, applying a sub-pipeline to each of these streams, and assembling the results into a corresponding output array stream.

Template Parameters
TInType of input array element.
TOutType of output array element.
Parameters
sourceSource stream.
vectorSizeVector arity.
streamTransformFunction mapping from an index and stream of input element to a stream of output element.
outputDefaultIfDroppedWhen true, a result is produced even if a message is dropped in processing one of the input elements. In this case the corresponding output element is set to a default value.
defaultValueDefault value to use when messages are dropped in processing one of the input elements.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
nameName for the parallel composite component (defaults to ParallelFixedLength).
defaultParallelDeliveryPolicyPipeline-level default delivery policy to be used by the parallel composite component (defaults to DeliveryPolicy.Unlimited if unspecified).
Returns
Stream of output arrays.

Executes a transform action for each item in the input stream. The action can output zero or more results by posting them to the emitter provided as an argument.

Template Parameters
TInThe input message type.
TOutThe output message type.
Parameters

Returns

◆ Sample< T >() [1/2]

static IProducer<T> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Sample< T > ( this IProducer< T >  source,
TimeSpan  samplingInterval,
RelativeTimeInterval  relativeTimeInterval = null,
DateTime?  alignmentDateTime = null,
DeliveryPolicy< T >  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Sample a stream at a given sampling interval, by selecting the nearest message within a relative time interval to the interpolation point.

Template Parameters
TType of source (and output) messages.
Parameters
sourceSource stream.
samplingIntervalInterval at which to apply the interpolator.
relativeTimeIntervalThe relative time interval within which to search for the nearest message. If the parameter is not specified the RelativeTimeInterval.Infiniterelative time interval is used,resulting in sampling the nearest point to the clock signal on the source stream.
alignmentDateTimeIf non-null, this parameter specifies a time to align the sampling messages with. If the parameter is non-null, the messages will have originating times that align with (i.e., are an integral number of intervals away from) the specified alignment time.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Sampled stream.

◆ Window< TSource, TWindow >()

static IProducer<Message<TSource>[]> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Window< TSource, TWindow > ( this IProducer< TSource >  source,
IProducer< TWindow >  window,
Func< Message< TWindow >,(TimeInterval, DateTime)>  windowCreator,
DeliveryPolicy< TSource >  sourceDeliveryPolicy = null,
DeliveryPolicy< TWindow >  windowDeliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Get windows of messages specified via data from an additional window-defining stream.

The operator implements dynamic windowing over a stream of data. Messages on the incoming window stream are used to compute a relative time interval in the source stream. The output is created by a function that has access to the window message and the computed buffer of messages on the source stream.

Template Parameters
TSourceType of source messages.
TWindowType of messages on the additional window stream.
Parameters
sourceThe source stream.
windowThe window-defining stream.
windowCreatorThe function that creates the actual window to use at every point.
sourceDeliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy for the source stream.
windowDeliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy for the window-defining stream.
Returns
A stream of computed outputs.

◆ Window< TSource, TWindow, TOutput >()

static IProducer<TOutput> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Window< TSource, TWindow, TOutput > ( this IProducer< TSource >  source,
IProducer< TWindow >  window,
Func< Message< TWindow >,(TimeInterval, DateTime)>  windowCreator,
Func< Message< TWindow >, IEnumerable< Message< TSource >>, TOutput >  outputCreator,
DeliveryPolicy< TSource >  sourceDeliveryPolicy = null,
DeliveryPolicy< TWindow >  windowDeliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Get windows of messages specified via data from an additional window-defining stream.

The operator implements dynamic windowing over a stream of data. Messages on the incoming window stream are used to compute a relative time interval in the source stream. The output is created by a function that has access to the window message and the computed buffer of messages on the source stream.

Template Parameters
TSourceType of source messages.
TWindowType of messages on the additional window stream.
TOutputType of messages on the output stream.
Parameters
sourceThe source stream.
windowThe window-defining stream.
windowCreatorThe function that creates the actual window to use at every point.
outputCreatorA function that creates output messages given a message on the window-defining stream and a buffer of messages on the source stream.
sourceDeliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy for the source stream.
windowDeliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy for the window-defining stream.
Returns
A stream of computed outputs.

◆ Zip< T >() [1/2]

static IProducer<T[]> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Zip< T > ( IEnumerable< IProducer< T >>  inputs,
DeliveryPolicy< T >  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Zip one or more streams (T) into a single stream while ensuring delivery in originating time order.

Messages are produced in originating-time order; potentially delayed in wall-clock time. If multiple messages arrive with the same originating time, they are added in the output array in the order of stream ids.

Template Parameters
TType of messages.
Parameters
inputsCollection of input streams to zip.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of zipped messages.

◆ Zip< T >() [2/2]

static IProducer<T[]> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Zip< T > ( this IProducer< T >  input1,
IProducer< T >  input2,
DeliveryPolicy< T >  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Zip two streams (T) into a single stream while ensuring delivery in originating time order.

Messages are produced in originating-time order; potentially delayed in wall-clock time. If multiple messages arrive with the same originating time, they are added in the output array in the order of stream ids.

Template Parameters
TType of messages.
Parameters
input1First input stream.
input2Second input stream with same message type.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of zipped messages.
